original: The bluegill (Lepomis macrochirus), sometimes referred to as "bream", "brim", "sunny", or, as is common in Texas, "copper nose", is a species of North American freshwater fish, native to and commonly found in streams, rivers, lakes, ponds and wetlands east of the Rocky Mountains. It is the type species of the genus Lepomis (true sunfish), from the family Centrarchidae (sunfishes, crappies and black basses) in the order Centrarchiformes. Bluegills can grow up to 16 in (41 cm) long and about 4.5 lb (2.0 kg). While their color can vary from population to population, they typically have a very distinctive coloring, with deep blue and purple on the face and gill cover, dark olive-colored bands down the side, and a fiery orange to yellow belly. They are omnivorous and will consume anything they can fit in their mouth, but mostly feed on small aquatic insects and baitfishes. The fish are important prey for bass, other larger sunfish, northern pike and muskellunge, walleye, trout, herons, kingfishers, snapping turtles and otters, and play a key role within the food chain of its freshwater ecosystem.

original:
Crayfish are freshwater crustaceans belonging to the infraorder Astacidea, which also contains lobsters. Taxonomically, they are members of the superfamilies Astacoidea and Parastacoidea. They breathe through feather-like gills. Some species are found in brooks and streams, where fresh water is running, while others thrive in swamps, ditches, and paddy fields. Most crayfish cannot tolerate polluted water, although some species, such as Procambarus clarkii, are hardier. Crayfish feed on animals and plants, either living or decomposing, and detritus.
Some kinds of crayfish are known locally as lobsters, crawdads, mudbugs, and yabbies. In the Eastern United States, "crayfish" is more common in the north, while "crawdad" is heard more in central and southwestern regions, and "crawfish" farther south, although considerable overlaps exist.

original: Micropterus is a genus of North American freshwater fish collectively known as the black bass, which belong to the sunfish family Centrarchidae of order Centrarchiformes. They are sometimes erroneously called "black trout", but the name trout more correctly refers to certain potamodromous members of the family Salmonidae. Micropterus are widely distributed east of the Rocky Mountains, from the Hudson Bay basin in Canada to northeastern Mexico. Several species, notably the largemouth and smallmouth bass, have been very widely introduced throughout the world, and are now considered cosmopolitan. All black bass species are highly sought-after game fish and well known as strong fighters when hooked, and bass fishing is an extremely popular outdoor sport throughout their native range. Their meat is quite edible and firm, although they are not regarded as commercial food fish.

original: The flathead catfish (Pylodictis olivaris), also called by several common names including mudcat or shovelhead cat, is a large species of North American freshwater catfish in the family Ictaluridae. It is the only species of the genus Pylodictis. Ranging from the lower Great Lakes region to northern Mexico, it has been widely introduced and is an invasive species in some areas. The closest living relative of the flathead catfish is the much smaller widemouth blindcat, Satan eurystomus, a cavefish.

original: Fathead minnow (Pimephales promelas), also known as fathead or tuffy, is a species of temperate freshwater fish belonging to the genus Pimephales of the cyprinid family. The natural geographic range extends throughout much of North America, from central Canada south along the Rockies to Texas, and east to Virginia and the Northeastern United States. This minnow has also been introduced to many other areas via bait bucket releases. Its golden, or xanthic, strain, known as the rosy-red minnow, is a very common feeder fish sold in the United States and Canada. This fish is also known for producing Schreckstoff (a distress signal).
english: Fathead minnow (Pimephales promelas), also known as fathead or tuffy, is a species of temperate freshwater fish belonging to the genus Pimephales of the cyprinid family. This minnow has also been introduced to many other areas via bait bucket releases. Its golden, or xanthic, strain, known as the rosy-red minnow, is a very common feeder fish sold in the United States and Canada. This fish is also known for producing Schreckstoff (a distress signal).

original:
The northern pike (Esox lucius) is a species of carnivorous fish of the genus Esox (pikes). They are commonly found in moderately salty and fresh waters of the Northern Hemisphere (i.e. holarctic in distribution). They are known simply as a pike (PL: pike) in Great Britain, Ireland, most of Eastern Europe, Canada and the U.S., although in the Midwest, they may be called a Northern.

Pike can grow to a relatively large size. Their average length is about 40�55 cm (16�22 in), with maximum recorded lengths of up to 150 cm (59 in) and maximum weights of 28.4 kg (63 lb). The IGFA currently recognises a 25 kg (55 lb) pike caught by Lothar Louis on Greffern Lake, Germany, on 16 October 1986, as the all-tackle world-record holding northern pike. Northern pike grow to larger sizes in Eurasia than in North America, and in coastal Eurasian regions than inland ones.

original:
The yellow perch (Perca flavescens), commonly referred to as perch, striped perch, American perch or preacher is a freshwater perciform fish native to much of North America. The yellow perch was described in 1814 by Samuel Latham Mitchill from New York. It is closely related, and morphologically similar to the European perch (Perca fluviatilis); and is sometimes considered a subspecies of its European counterpart.

Latitudinal variability in age, growth rates, and size have been observed among populations of yellow perch, likely resulting from differences in day length and annual water temperatures. In many populations, yellow perch often live 9 to 10 years, with adults generally ranging 4�10 in (10�25 cm) in length.

original: The sauger (Sander canadensis) is a freshwater perciform fish of the family Percidae that resembles its close relative, the walleye. The species is a member of the largest vertebrate order, the Perciformes. It is the most migratory percid species in North America. Saugers have two dorsal fins; the first is spiny and the posterior dorsal fin is soft-rayed. Their paired fins are in the thoracic position and their caudal fin is truncated, which means squared off at the corners, a characteristic of the family Percidae. Another physical characteristic of saugers is their ctenoid scales, which are common in advanced fishes. Saugers have a fusiform body structure, and as a result are well adapted predatory fishes and are capable of swimming into fast currents with minimal drag on their bodies. They may be distinguished from walleyes by the distinctly spotted dorsal fin, by the lack of a white splotch on the caudal fin, by the rough skin over their gills, and by their generally more brassy color, or darker (almost black) color in some regions. The typical sauger is 300 to 400 g (11 to 14 oz) in weight.

italian: Il Sauger è un pesce perciforme d'acqua dolce della famiglia Percidae che ricorda il suo parente stretto, il glaucoma. La specie è un membro del più grande ordine di vertebrati, i Perciformi. è la specie percida più migratrice del Nord America.
spanish: El Sauger es un pez perciforme de agua dulce de la familia Percidae que se parece a su pariente cercano, la lucioperca. La especie es miembro del orden de vertebrados más grande, los Perciformes. Es la especie de pércido más migratoria de América del Norte.
french: Le Sauger est un poisson perciforme d'eau douce de la famille des Percidae qui ressemble à son proche parent, le doré jaune. L'espèce fait partie du plus grand ordre de vertébrés, les Perciformes. C'est l'espèce de percidé la plus migratrice d'Amérique du Nord.
chinese: Sauger是Percidae科的一種淡水鱸形魚，類似於它的近親，角膜白斑。該物種是最大的脊椎動物目 Perciformes 的成員。它是北美遷徙最多的鱸魚物種。

portuguese: O Sauger é um peixe perciforme de água doce da família Percidae que se assemelha ao seu parente próximo, o walleye. A espécie é membro da maior ordem de vertebrados, os Perciformes. é a espécie de percídeo mais migratória da América do Norte.

original:
The rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss) is a species of trout native to cold-water tributaries of the Pacific Ocean in North America and Asia. The steelhead (sometimes called steelhead trout) is an anadromous (sea-run) form of the coastal rainbow trout (O. m. irideus) or Columbia River redband trout (O. m. gairdneri) that usually returns to freshwater to spawn after living two to three years in the ocean. Freshwater forms that have been introduced into the Great Lakes and migrate into tributaries to spawn are also called steelhead.

Adult freshwater stream rainbow trout average between 0.5 and 2.5 kilograms (1 and 5 lb), while lake-dwelling and anadromous forms may reach 9 kg (20 lb). Coloration varies widely based on subspecies, forms, and habitat. Adult fish are distinguished by a broad reddish stripe along the lateral line, from gills to the tail, which is most vivid in breeding males.
english:

Freshwater forms that have been introduced into the Great Lakes and migrate into tributaries to spawn are also called steelhead.

Adult freshwater stream rainbow trout average between 0.5 and 2.5 kilograms (1 and 5 lb), while lake-dwelling and anadromous forms may reach 9 kg (20 lb). Coloration varies widely based on subspecies, forms, and habitat. Adult fish are distinguished by a broad reddish stripe along the lateral line, from gills to the tail, which is most vivid in breeding males.

original: The white bass, silver bass, or sand bass (Morone chrysops) is a freshwater fish of the temperate bass family Moronidae. commonly around 12�15 inches long. The species' main color is silver-white to pale green. Its back is dark, with white sides and belly, and with narrow dark stripes running lengthwise on its sides. It has large, rough scales and two dorsal fins. They are widely distributed across North America, inhabiting large reservoirs and rivers. When mating in the spring, they are more often found in shallow rivers, creeks, and streams. They have been introduced in some places as sport fish and also to predate on nuisance fish, such as gizzard shad. It is the state fish of Oklahoma.
english: The white bass, silver bass, or sand bass (Morone chrysops) is a freshwater fish of the temperate bass family Moronidae. commonly around 12�15 inches long. The species' main color is silver-white to pale green. Its back is dark, with white sides and belly, and with narrow dark stripes running lengthwise on its sides. It has large, rough scales and two dorsal fins. They are widely distributed across North America, inhabiting large reservoirs and rivers. When mating in the spring, they are more often found in shallow rivers, creeks, and streams. They have been introduced in some places as sport fish and also to predate on nuisance fish, such as gizzard shad. It is the state fish of Oklahoma.

Jeho h?bet je tmavy, s bílymi boky a b?ichem a s úzkymi tmavymi pruhy podél jeho stran. Má velké, drsné ?upiny a dvě h?betní ploutve. P?edněj?í h?betní ploutev je mnohem tvrd?í a zdá se, ?e má na sobě trny. P?esto?e se nejedná o pravé trny, tento typ ploutví se nazyvá trnovy paprsek. Zadní ze dvou h?betních ploutví je mnohem měk?í, a proto se nazyvá měkky paprsek.
german: Der Wei?barsch ist ein Sü?wasserfisch der gem??igten Barschfamilie Moronidae. Die Hauptfarbe der Art ist silberwei? bis blassgrün. Sein Rücken ist dunkel, mit wei?en Seiten und Bauch und mit schmalen dunklen Streifen, die l?ngs an seinen Seiten verlaufen. Es hat gro?e, grobe Schuppen und zwei Rückenflossen. Die weiter vorne liegende Rückenflosse ist viel h?rter und scheint Stacheln zu haben. Obwohl dies keine echten Stacheln sind, wird diese Art von Flossen als Stachelrochen bezeichnet. russian: Белый окунь — пресноводная рыба семейства окуней умеренного пояса Moronidae. Основной цвет вида от серебристо-белого до бледно-зеленого. Спина у него темная, с белыми боками и брюхом и с узкими темными полосами, идущими вдоль по бокам. У него крупная грубая чешуя и два спинных плавника. Более передний спинной плавник намного тверже и, кажется, имеет шипы на нем. Хотя это не настоящие шипы, этот тип плавника называется шипастым лучом. Более задний из двух спинных плавников намного мягче, поэтому его называют мягким лучом.
polish: Gatunek s?odkowodnej, drapie?nej ryby okoniokszta?tnej z rodziny bassowatych. W Polsce jest gatunkiem sztucznie przywiezionym. Widywany w Odrze i jej dop?ywach. Zosta? sztucznie zasiedlony w Dolnej Odrze w Gryfinie gdzie odbywa tar?o.
hungarian: A fehér sügér a Moronidae mérsékelt ?vi sügér családjába tartozó édesvízi hal. A faj f? színe ezüstfehért?l halványz?ldig terjed. Háta s?tét, oldalai és hasa fehér, oldalain hosszában keskeny, s?tét csíkokkal. Nagy, durva pikkelyei és két hátúszója van. Az elüls? hátúszó sokkal keményebb, és úgy t?nik, hogy tüskék vannak rajtuk. Bár ezek nem valódi tüskék, az ilyen típusú uszonyokat tüskés sugárnak nevezik. A két hátúszó k?zül a hátulsó sokkal lágyabb, ezért lágysugárnak nevezik.
italian: Il White Bass è un pesce d'acqua dolce della famiglia dei Moronidae. Il colore principale della specie va dal bianco argento al verde pallido. Il dorso è scuro, con i fianchi e il ventre bianchi e con strette strisce scure che corrono longitudinalmente ai lati. Ha squame grandi e ruvide e due pinne dorsali. La pinna dorsale più anteriore è molto più dura e sembra avere spine su di esse. Sebbene queste non siano vere spine, questo tipo di pinna è chiamato raggio spinoso. La più posteriore delle due pinne dorsali è molto più morbida ed è quindi chiamata raggio molle.
spanish: La lubina blanca es un pez de agua dulce de la familia de las lubinas templadas Moronidae. El color principal de la especie es de color blanco plateado a verde pálido. Su dorso es oscuro, con los costados y el vientre blancos, y con estrechas rayas oscuras que corren a lo largo de los costados. Tiene escamas grandes y ásperas y dos aletas dorsales. La aleta dorsal más anterior es mucho más dura y parece tener espinas. Aunque estas no son verdaderas espinas, este tipo de aleta se llama radio espinoso. La más posterior de las dos aletas dorsales es mucho más suave y, por lo tanto, se denomina radio suave.
french: Le bar blanc est un poisson d'eau douce de la famille des bars tempérés Moronidae. La couleur principale de l'espèce est blanc argenté à vert pale. Son dos est sombre, avec des flancs et un ventre blancs, et de fines rayures sombres s'étendant dans le sens de la longueur sur ses c?tés. Il a de grandes écailles rugueuses et deux nageoires dorsales. La nageoire dorsale la plus antérieure est beaucoup plus dure et semble avoir des épines. Bien qu'il ne s'agisse pas de véritables épines, ce type de nageoire est appelé rayon épineux. La plus postérieure des deux nageoires dorsales est beaucoup plus molle et est donc appelée rayon mou.
chinese: 白鱸魚是溫帶鱸魚科Moronidae 的淡水魚。該物種的主要顏色是銀白色到淡綠色。它的背部是黑色的，有白色的側面和腹部，兩側有縱向延伸的狹窄黑色條紋。它有大而粗糙的鱗片和兩個背鰭。更前背鰭更硬，似乎有刺。雖然這些不是真正的刺，但這種類型的鰭被稱為棘鰭。兩個背鰭中靠後的那個軟得多，因此被稱為軟鰭。
japanese: ホワイトバスは、温帯低木科モロン属の淡水魚である。本種の主な体色は銀白色から淡緑色である。背中は黒っぽく、側面と腹は白く、側面には縦に走る細い暗色の縞模様がある。大きな粗い鱗があり、背びれは2つある。より前方の背びれはかなり硬く、棘があるように見える。これは本当の棘ではないが、このタイプの鰭は棘条と呼ばれる。後方の背ビレはかなり柔らかく、ソフトレイと呼ばれる。
portuguese: O White Bass é um peixe de água doce da família do baixo temperado Moronidae. A cor principal da espécie é de branco prateado a verde pálido. O dorso é escuro, com os lados e a barriga brancos, e com listras escuras estreitas que correm longitudinalmente nas laterais. Tem escamas grandes e ásperas e duas barbatanas dorsais. A barbatana dorsal mais anterior é muito mais dura e parece ter espinhos. Embora n?o sejam espinhos verdadeiros, esse tipo de barbatana é chamado de raio espinhoso. A mais posterior das duas barbatanas dorsais é muito mais macia e, portanto, é chamada de raio mole.
chinesesimp: 白鲈鱼是温带鲈鱼科Moronidae 的淡水鱼。该物种的主要颜色是银白色到淡绿色。它的背部是黑色的，有白色的侧面和腹部，两侧有纵向延伸的狭窄黑色条纹。它有大而粗糙的鳞片和两个背鳍。更前背鳍更硬，似乎有刺。虽然这些不是真正的刺，但这种类型的鳍被称为棘鳍。两个背鳍中靠后的那个软得多，因此被称为软鳍。

original: The bowfin (Amia calva) is a ray-finned fish native to North America. Common names include mudfish, mud pike, dogfish, grindle, grinnel, swamp trout, and choupique. It is regarded as a relict, being one of only two surviving species of the Halecomorphi, a group of fish that first appeared during the Early Triassic, around 250 million years ago. The bowfin is often considered a "living fossil" because they have retained some morphological characteristics of their early ancestors. It is one of two species in the genus Amia, along with Amia ocellicauda, the eyespot bowfin. The closest living relatives of bowfins are gars, with the two groups being united in the clade Holostei.
english: The bowfin (Amia calva) is a ray-finned fish native to North America. Common names include mudfish, mud pike, dogfish, grindle, grinnel, swamp trout, and choupique. It is regarded as a relict, being one of only two surviving species of the Halecomorphi, a group of fish that first appeared during the Early Triassic, around 250 million years ago. The bowfin is often considered a "living fossil" because they have retained some morphological characteristics of their early ancestors. It is one of two species in the genus Amia, along with Amia ocellicauda, the eyespot bowfin. The closest living relatives of bowfins are gars, with the two groups being united in the clade Holostei.

french: Le Bowfin est un poisson osseux, originaire d'Amérique du Nord. Il est considéré comme une relique, étant la seule espèce survivante des Halecomorphi, un groupe de poissons apparu pour la première fois au début du Trias, il y a environ 250 millions d'années.
chinese: 弓鰭魚是一種硬骨魚，原產於北美。常見的名稱包括泥魚、泥梭魚、角鯊、grindle、grinnel、沼澤鱒魚和 choupique。它被認為是一種遺物，是 Halecomorphi 中唯一倖存的物種，Halecomorphi 是一種在大約 2.5 億年前的三疊紀早期首次出現的魚類。
japanese: ボウフィン（アミア?カルヴァ）は、北アメリカ原産の硬骨魚。マッドフィッシュ、マッドパイク、ドッグフィッシュ、グリンドル、グリンネル、スワンプトラウト、シュピケなどの俗称がある。約2億5000万年前の初期三畳紀に出現したHalecomorphiという魚類の唯一の現存種であり、遺物とみなされている。

chinesesimp: 弓鳍鱼是一种硬骨鱼，原产于北美。常见的名称包括泥鱼、泥梭鱼、角鲨、grindle、grinnel、沼泽鳟鱼和 choupique。它被认为是一种遗物，是 Halecomorphi 中唯一幸存的物种，Halecomorphi 是一种在大约 2.5 亿年前的三叠纪早期首次出现的鱼类。

original: The slimy sculpin (Cottus cognatus) is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the family Cottidae, which is the largest sculpin family. They usually inhabit cold rocky streams or lakes across North America, ranging from the Great Lakes, southeast Minnesota, northeast Iowa, southwest Wisconsin and northeast Canada. Slimy sculpins have also been found roaming the cold streams of eastern Siberia. They are commonly confused with their closely related relatives, Mottled sculpin (Cottus bairdi), and with tubenose gobies who are both freshwater fishes as well. The slimy sculpin is a nocturnal fish that usually spends most of its time on the stream bottom and seeks shelter under rocks and logs, especially during spawning season. When it swims, it sometimes appears to be "hopping" along the bottom because of its inefficient ability to swim. This is partly due to the absence of a swim bladder, which normally gives buoyancy to a fish.

When it swims, it sometimes appears to be "hopping" along the bottom because of its inefficient ability to swim. Sie bewohnen normalerweise kalte felsige B?che oder Seen in ganz Nordamerika, die von den Gro?en Seen über Südost-Minnesota, Nordost-Iowa, Südwest-Wisconsin und Nordost-Kanada reichen.

Обычно они населяют холодные скалистые ручьи или озера по всей Северной Америке, начиная от Великих озер, юго-востока Миннесоты, северо-востока Айовы, юго-запада Висконсина и северо-востока Канады.

italian: Lo sculpin viscido è una specie di pesce d'acqua dolce appartenente alla famiglia Cottidae, che è la più grande famiglia di sculpin. Di solito abitano torrenti o laghi rocciosi freddi in tutto il Nord America, che vanno dai Grandi Laghi, al Minnesota sud-orientale, all'Iowa nord-orientale, al Wisconsin sud-occidentale e al Canada nord-orientale.
spanish: El sculpin baboso es una especie de pez de agua dulce que pertenece a la familia Cottidae, que es la familia sculpin más grande. Por lo general, habitan arroyos o lagos rocosos fríos en América del Norte, desde los Grandes Lagos, el sureste de Minnesota, el noreste de Iowa, el suroeste de Wisconsin y el noreste de Canadá.

chinese: 泥鰍魚是一種淡水魚類，屬於最大的鯰魚科科特科。它們通常棲息在北美寒冷的岩石溪流或湖泊中，範圍從五大湖、明尼蘇達州東南部、愛荷華州東北部、威斯康星州西南部和加拿大東北部。
japanese: スライミースカルピン（Cottus cognatus）は、カジカ目カジカ科に属する淡水魚の一種である。通常、五大湖からミネソタ州南東部、アイオワ州北東部、ウィスコンシン州南西部、カナダ北東部にかけての北米各地の冷たい岩場の流れや湖に生息している。
portuguese: O escultor viscoso é uma espécie de peixe de água doce pertencente à família Cottidae, que é a maior família de esculturas. Eles geralmente habitam riachos ou lagos rochosos frios em toda a América do Norte, desde os Grandes Lagos, sudeste de Minnesota, nordeste de Iowa, sudoeste de Wisconsin e nordeste do Canadá.
chinesesimp: 泥鳅鱼是一种淡水鱼类，属于最大的鲶鱼科科特科。它们通常栖息在北美寒冷的岩石溪流或湖泊中，范围从五大湖、明尼苏达州东南部、爱荷华州东北部、威斯康星州西南部和加拿大东北部。

original: Mussel is the common name used for members of several families of bivalve molluscs, from saltwater and freshwater habitats. These groups have in common a shell whose outline is elongated and asymmetrical compared with other edible clams, which are often more or less rounded or oval.
english: Mussel is the common name used for members of several families of bivalve molluscs, from saltwater and freshwater habitats. These groups have in common a shell whose outline is elongated and asymmetrical compared with other edible clams, which are often more or less rounded or oval.

original: Angel Fish, particularly tilapia, are important food fishes, while others, such as the Cichla species, are valued game fish. The family also includes many popular freshwater aquarium fish kept by hobbyists, including the angelfish, oscars, and discus.
english: Angel Fish, particularly tilapia, are important food fishes, while others, such as the Cichla species, are valued game fish. The family also includes many popular freshwater aquarium fish kept by hobbyists, including the angelfish, oscars, and discus.

italian: I pesci angelo, in particolare la tilapia, sono importanti pesci alimentari, mentre altri, come la specie Cichla, sono pregiati pesci selvaggi. La famiglia comprende anche molti famosi pesci d'acquario d'acqua dolce tenuti da hobbisti, inclusi pesci angelo, oscar e discus.

La familia también incluye muchos peces de acuario de agua dulce populares mantenidos por aficionados, incluidos el pez ángel, los oscar y el disco.
french: Les poissons-anges, en particulier le tilapia, sont des poissons de consommation importants, tandis que d'autres, comme l'espèce Cichla, sont des poissons de gibier appréciés. La famille comprend également de nombreux poissons d'aquarium d'eau douce populaires gardés par les amateurs, notamment les poissons-anges, les oscars et les discus.

A família também inclui muitos peixes populares de aquário de água doce mantidos por amadores, incluindo o peixe-anjo, o oscar e o disco.

original: Blue marlin are distributed throughout the tropical and subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean. A bluewater fish that spends the majority of its life in the open sea far from land, the blue marlin preys on a wide variety of marine organisms, mostly near the surface, often using its bill to stun or injure its prey. Way too heavy to carry!
english: Blue marlin are distributed throughout the tropical and subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean. A bluewater fish that spends the majority of its life in the open sea far from land, the blue marlin preys on a wide variety of marine organisms, mostly near the surface, often using its bill to stun or injure its prey. Way too heavy to carry!

german: Blue Marline sind in den tropischen und subtropischen Gew?ssern des Atlantischen Ozeans verbreitet. Охотится на множество морских организмов, в основном у поверхности, часто используя свой клюв, чтобы оглушить или ранить добычу. Слишком тяжелый для ношения!

italian: Il marlin blu è distribuito nelle acque tropicali e subtropicali dell'Oceano Atlantico. Pesce d'acqua blu che trascorre la maggior parte della sua vita in mare aperto lontano dalla terraferma, il marlin blu preda un'ampia varietà di organismi marini, per lo più vicino alla superficie, spesso usando il becco per stordire o ferire la sua preda. Troppo pesante da trasportare!
spanish: El Marlín azul se distribuye por las aguas tropicales y subtropicales del Océano Atlántico. Un pez de agua azul que pasa la mayor parte de su vida en mar abierto lejos de la tierra, el marlin azul se alimenta de una amplia variedad de organismos marinos, principalmente cerca de la superficie, a menudo usando su pico para aturdir o herir a su presa. ˇDemasiado pesado para llevar!
french: Le makaire bleu est réparti dans les eaux tropicales et subtropicales de l'océan Atlantique. Poisson d'eau bleue qui passe la majeure partie de sa vie en haute mer loin de la terre, le makaire bleu se nourrit d'une grande variété d'organismes marins, principalement près de la surface, utilisant souvent son bec pour étourdir ou blesser ses proies. Bien trop lourd à porter !
chinese: 藍槍魚分佈於大西洋的熱帶和亞熱帶水域。藍槍魚是一種藍水魚，大部分時間都在遠離陸地的公海中度過， 藍槍魚捕食各種海洋生物，主要是在地表附近，經常用它的喙來擊暈或傷害獵物。太重了，搬不動！

portuguese: O espadim azul está distribuído pelas águas tropicais e subtropicais do Oceano Atlantico. Um peixe de água azul que passa a maior parte de sua vida em mar aberto, longe da terra, o espadim azul ataca uma grande variedade de organismos marinhos, principalmente perto da superfície, muitas vezes usando seu bico para atordoar ou ferir suas presas. Muito pesado para carregar!

english: Bonitos are a tribe of medium-sized, ray-finned predatory fish in the family Scombridae � a family it shares with the mackerel, tuna, and Spanish mackerel tribes, and also the butterfly kingfish.

english: The masu salmon, also known as masu or cherry trout in Japan, is a species of salmon belonging to the genus Oncorhynchus, found in the North Pacific along Northeast/East Asian coasts from the Russian Far East to south through Korea, Japan and Taiwan.

english: The Flathead Mullet is an important food fish species in the mullet family Mugilidae. It is found in coastal tropical and subtropical waters worldwide. Its length is typically 30 to 75 centimetres.

portuguese: A Tainha-chata é uma importante espécie de peixe alimentar da família das tainhas Mugilidae. é encontrado em águas costeiras tropicais e subtropicais em todo o mundo. Seu comprimento é tipicamente de 30 a 75 centímetros.
chinesesimp: 鲻鱼是鲻科鲻鱼科的重要食用鱼种。它存在于世界各地的沿海热带和亚热带水域。它的长度通常为 30 至 75 厘米。

spanish: El tiburón leopardo (Triakis semifasciata) es una especie de tiburón, de la familia Triakidae. Bien trop lourd à porter !

original: The Pacific Cod, Gadus macrocephalus, is a species of ray-finned fish in the family Gadidae. It is a bottom-dwelling fish found in the northern Pacific Ocean, mainly on the continental shelf and upper slopes, to depths of about 900 m. It can grow to a length of a meter or so and is found in large schools.
english: The Pacific Cod, Gadus macrocephalus, is a species of ray-finned fish in the family Gadidae. It is a bottom-dwelling fish found in the northern Pacific Ocean, mainly on the continental shelf and upper slopes, to depths of about 900 m. It can grow to a length of a meter or so and is found in large schools.

Je to ryba ?ijící u dna, která se vyskytuje v severním Tichém oceánu, hlavně na kontinentálním ?elfu a horních svazích, do hloubek asi 900 m. M??e dor?st a? do délky jednoho metru a vyskytuje se ve velkych ?kolách.

Es ist ein am Boden lebender Fisch, der im n?rdlichen Pazifischen Ozean vor allem auf dem Festlandsockel und den oberen H?ngen bis in Tiefen von etwa 900 m vorkommt. Er kann bis zu einem Meter lang werden und kommt in gro?en Schw?rmen vor.

Это донная рыба, обитающая в северной части Тихого океана, в основном на континентальном шельфе и верхних склонах, до глубин около 900 м. Он может вырасти до метра или около того и встречается в больших стаях.

italian: Il merluzzo del Pacifico, Gadus macrocephalus, è una specie di pesce con pinne raggiate della famiglia Gadidae. è un pesce di fondo che si trova nell'Oceano Pacifico settentrionale, principalmente sulla piattaforma continentale e sui pendii superiori, fino a una profondità di circa 900 m. Può raggiungere una lunghezza di circa un metro e si trova in grandi scuole.
spanish: El bacalao del Pacífico, Gadus macrocephalus, es una especie de pez con aletas radiadas de la familia Gadidae. Es un pez que vive en el fondo y se encuentra en el Océano Pacífico norte, principalmente en la plataforma continental y los taludes superiores, a profundidades de unos 900 m. Puede crecer hasta una longitud de un metro más o menos y se encuentra en grandes cardúmenes.
french: La morue du Pacifique, Gadus macrocephalus, est une espèce de poisson à nageoires rayonnées de la famille des Gadidae. C'est un poisson de fond que l'on trouve dans le nord de l'océan Pacifique, principalement sur le plateau continental et les pentes supérieures, jusqu'à des profondeurs d'environ 900 m. Il peut atteindre une longueur d'environ un mètre et se trouve dans les grands bancs.
chinese: 太平洋鱈魚（學名Gadus macrocephalus）是鰩科鰩科的一種鰭魚。它是一種生活在北太平洋的底棲魚類，主要分佈在大陸架和上坡，深度約 900 m。它可以長到一米左右的長度，並在大型學校中發現。
japanese: マダラ(Gadus macrocephalus)は、マダラ科の鰭脚魚類の一種である。太平洋北部の主に大陸棚や上部斜面から水深約900mに生息する底棲魚で、体長は1mほどになり、大きな群れをなして生息している。
portuguese: O Bacalhau do Pacífico, Gadus macrocephalus, é uma espécie de peixe da família Gadidae. é um peixe de fundo encontrado no norte do Oceano Pacífico, principalmente na plataforma continental e nas encostas superiores, a profundidades de cerca de 900 m. Pode crescer até um metro de comprimento ou mais e é encontrado em grandes escolas.
chinesesimp: 太平洋鳕鱼（学名Gadus macrocephalus）是鳐科鳐科的一种鳍鱼。它是一种生活在北太平洋的底栖鱼类，主要分布在大陆架和上坡，深度约 900 m。它可以长到一米左右的长度，并在大型学校中发现。

hungarian: A Vieja melanurus, a quetzal sügér, v?r?s hajú sügér vagy t?zfej? sügér egy sügérfaj, amely a Petén-tó rendszerében, a Grijalva–Usumacinta folyó medencéjében és más Atlanti-óceáni folyók lecsapolásaiban ?shonos Mexikó déli részén, Belize-ben és Guatemalában, betelepített populációival. néhány másik ország.
italian: Vieja melanurus, il ciclide quetzal, ciclide rosso o ciclide testa di fuoco, è una specie di ciclide originaria del sistema del lago Petén, del bacino del fiume Grijalva-Usumacinta e di altri drenaggi fluviali atlantici nel Messico meridionale, Belize e Guatemala, con popolazioni introdotte in pochi altri paesi.
spanish: Vieja melanurus, el cíclido quetzal, cíclido pelirrojo o cíclido cabeza de fuego, es una especie de cíclido nativa del sistema del lago Petén, la cuenca del río Grijalva-Usumacinta y otros drenajes de ríos del Atlántico en el sur de México, Belice y Guatemala, con poblaciones introducidas en algunos otros países.
french: Vieja melanurus , le cichlidé quetzal , le cichlidé roux ou le cichlidé à tête de feu , est une espèce de cichlidé originaire du système du lac Petén , du bassin de la rivière Grijalva – Usumacinta et d'autres bassins fluviaux de l'Atlantique dans le sud du Mexique , Belize et Guatemala , avec des populations introduites dans quelques autres pays.

portuguese: Vieja melanurus, o ciclídeo quetzal, ciclídeo ruivo ou ciclídeo cabe?a-de-fogo, é uma espécie de ciclídeo nativa do sistema do Lago Petén, da bacia do rio Grijalva-Usumacinta e outras drenagens de rios atlanticos no sul do México, Belize e Guatemala, com popula??es introduzidas em alguns outros países.
chinesesimp: Vieja melanurus，格查尔慈鲷、红头慈鲷或火头慈鲷，是一种原产于佩滕湖系统、Grijalva-Usumacinta 河流域和墨西哥南部、伯利兹和危地马拉的其他大西洋河流流域的慈鲷物种。其他几个国家。

english: The rougheye rockfish (Sebastes aleutianus) is a rockfish of the genus Sebastes. It is also known as the blackthroat rockfish or the blacktip rockfish and grows to a maximum of about 97 cm.

original:
Tegillarca granosa (also known as Anadara granosa) is a species of ark clam known as the blood cockle or blood clam due to the red haemoglobin liquid inside the soft tissues. It is found throughout the Indo-Pacific region from the eastern coast of South Africa northwards and eastwards to Southeast Asia, Australia, Polynesia, and up to northern Japan. It lives mainly in the intertidal zone at one to two metres water depth, burrowed down into sand or mud. Adult size is about 5 to 6 cm long and 4 to 5 cm wide.

The meat of this bivalve is served steamed, boiled, roasted, or traditionally raw.

It is found throughout the Indo-Pacific region from the eastern coast of South Africa northwards and eastwards to Southeast Asia, Australia, Polynesia, and up to northern Japan. It lives mainly in the intertidal zone at one to two metres water depth, burrowed down into sand or mud. Adult size is about 5 to 6 cm long and 4 to 5 cm wide.

The meat of this bivalve is served steamed, boiled, roasted, or traditionally raw.

original: King crabs are decapod crustaceans of the family Lithodidae[b] that are chiefly found in deep waters and are adapted to cold environments. They are composed of two subfamilies: Lithodinae, which tend to inhabit deep waters, are globally distributed, and comprise the majority of the family's species diversity; and Hapalogastrinae, which are endemic to the North Pacific and inhabit exclusively shallow waters. King crabs superficially resemble true crabs but are generally understood to be closest to the pagurid hermit crabs. This placement of king crabs among the hermit crabs is supported by several anatomical peculiarities which are present only in king crabs and hermit crabs, making them a prominent example of carcinisation among decapods. Several species of king crabs, especially in Alaskan and southern South American waters, are targeted by commercial fisheries and have been subject to overfishing.
english: King crabs are decapod crustaceans of the family Lithodidae[b] that are chiefly found in deep waters and are adapted to cold environments. They are composed of two subfamilies: Lithodinae, which tend to inhabit deep waters, are globally distributed, and comprise the majority of the family's species diversity; and Hapalogastrinae, which are endemic to the North Pacific and inhabit exclusively shallow waters. King crabs superficially resemble true crabs but are generally understood to be closest to the pagurid hermit crabs. This placement of king crabs among the hermit crabs is supported by several anatomical peculiarities which are present only in king crabs and hermit crabs, making them a prominent example of carcinisation among decapods. Several species of king crabs, especially in Alaskan and southern South American waters, are targeted by commercial fisheries and have been subject to overfishing.

original: A crankbait has a short, stocky body typically with two treble hooks, but also an elongated elliptical bill that often equals or even exceeds the body length. When retrieved, the large bill will cause the lure to pitch down and dive, often accompanied by small, fast side-to-side twitches. The rate and depth of the dive depends on the design of the bill and the specific gravity of the lure's body (usually lighter than water). The name "crankbait" refers to the steady speed of the fisherman's reel cranking during retrieval, which imparts a linear dive on the lure, until the reeling stops (which causes the lure to float up).
english: A crankbait has a short, stocky body typically with two treble hooks, but also an elongated elliptical bill that often equals or even exceeds the body length. When retrieved, the large bill will cause the lure to pitch down and dive, often accompanied by small, fast side-to-side twitches. The rate and depth of the dive depends on the design of the bill and the specific gravity of the lure's body (usually lighter than water). The name "crankbait" refers to the steady speed of the fisherman's reel cranking during retrieval, which imparts a linear dive on the lure, until the reeling stops (which causes the lure to float up).

original: A jerkbait or "minnow" has a swimbait-like slender body that resembles a small bait fish (e.g. a shad), a short steeply angled bill, and usually two (or sometimes three) treble hooks. A jerkbait's bill is not large enough to make the whole lure dive, but if the fisherman flicks the rod and line during retrieval, the sudden brief acceleration causes the nose of the lure to easily decelerate, roll and yaw, thus imparting a stop-and-go, random "darting" motion ("jerks") that resembles the spasmodic struggle of an injured or dying fish.

original: The in-line spinner is named for the fact that a metal blade revolves around a central axis (a wire), which may be attached by a clevis (a c-shaped metal piece with holes that accommodates the wire) or by itself. Most in-line spinners have metal weights rigged behind the spinning blade and beads or brass hardware that separates the two for frictionless spinning. Due to the fact that the spinning blade cause the whole bait to rotate, line twist builds that creates line problems and tangles. Swivels are used to solve the problem of twist.

original:
The yellowfin tuna (Thunnus albacares) is a species of tuna found in pelagic waters of tropical and subtropical oceans worldwide.

Yellowfin is often marketed as ahi, from the Hawaiian ?ahi, a name also used there for the closely related bigeye tuna. The species name, albacares ("white meat") can also lead to confusion: in English, the albacore (Thunnus alalunga) is a different species, while yellowfin is officially designated albacore in French and referred to as albacora by Portuguese fishermen.

The yellowfin tuna is among the larger tuna species, reaching weights over 180 kg (400 lb), but is significantly smaller than the Atlantic and Pacific bluefin tunas, which can reach over 450 kg (990 lb), and slightly smaller than the bigeye tuna and the southern bluefin tuna.

original:
The brown trout (Salmo trutta) is a species of salmonid ray-finned fish and the most widely distributed species of the genus Salmo, endemic to most of Europe, West Asia and parts of North Africa, and has been widely introduced globally as a game fish, even becoming one of the world's worst invasive species outside of its native range.

Brown trout are highly adaptable and have evolved numerous ecotypes/subspecies. These include three main ecotypes: a riverine ecotype called river trout or Salmo trutta morpha fario; a lacustrine ecotype or S. trutta morpha lacustris, also called the lake trout (not to be confused with the lake trout in North America); and anadromous populations known as the sea trout or S. trutta morpha trutta, which upon adulthood migrate downstream to the oceans for much of its life and only returns to fresh water to spawn in the gravel beds of headstreams.[citation needed] Sea trout in Ireland and Great Britain have many regional names: sewin in Wales, finnock in Scotland, peal in the West Country, mort in North West England, and white trout in Ireland.

Brown trout are highly adaptable and have evolved numerous ecotypes/subspecies. These include three main ecotypes: a riverine ecotype called river trout or Salmo trutta morpha fario; a lacustrine ecotype or S. trutta morpha lacustris, also called the lake trout (not to be confused with the lake trout in North America); and anadromous populations known as the sea trout or S. trutta morpha trutta, which upon adulthood migrate downstream to the oceans for much of its life and only returns to fresh water to spawn in the gravel beds of headstreams.[citation needed] Sea trout in Ireland and Great Britain have many regional names: sewin in Wales, finnock in Scotland, peal in the West Country, mort in North West England, and white trout in Ireland.

original: The brook trout (Salvelinus fontinalis) is a species of freshwater fish in the char genus Salvelinus of the salmon family Salmonidae. It is native to Eastern North America in the United States and Canada, but has been introduced elsewhere in North America, as well as to Iceland, Europe, and Asia. In parts of its range, it is also known as the eastern brook trout, speckled trout, brook charr, squaretail, brookie or mud trout, among others. A potamodromous population in Lake Superior, as well as an anadromous population in Maine, is known as coaster trout or, simply, as coasters. The brook trout is the state fish of nine U.S. states: Michigan, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, Pennsylvania, Vermont, Virginia, and West Virginia, and the Provincial Fish of Nova Scotia in Canada.

original: The cutthroat trout (Oncorhynchus clarkii) is a fish species of the family Salmonidae native to cold-water tributaries of the Pacific Ocean, Rocky Mountains, and Great Basin in North America. As a member of the genus Oncorhynchus, it is one of the Pacific trout, a group that includes the widely distributed rainbow trout. Cutthroat trout are popular gamefish, especially among anglers who enjoy fly fishing. The common name "cutthroat" refers to the distinctive red coloration on the underside of the lower jaw. The specific name clarkii was given to honor explorer William Clark, coleader of the Lewis and Clark Expedition.

spanish: La trucha degollada (Oncorhynchus clarkii) es una especie de pez de la familia Salmonidae nativa de los afluentes de agua fría del Océano Pacífico, las Montañas Rocosas y la Gran Cuenca en América del Norte. Como miembro del género Oncorhynchus, pertenece a la trucha del Pacífico, un grupo que incluye la trucha arco iris de amplia distribución. La trucha degollada es un pez deportivo popular, especialmente entre los pescadores que disfrutan de la pesca con mosca. El nombre común "asesino" se refiere a la coloración roja distintiva en la parte inferior de la mandíbula inferior. El nombre específico clarkii se le dio en honor al explorador William Clark, colíder de la Expedición Lewis y Clark.
french: La truite fardée (Oncorhynchus clarkii) est une espèce de poisson de la famille des Salmonidae originaires de affluents d'eau froide de l'océan Pacifique, des montagnes rocheuses et du grand bassin en Amérique du Nord. En tant que membre du genre Oncorhynchus, c'est l'une des truites du Pacifique, un groupe qui comprend la truite arc-en-ciel largement distribuée. La truite fardée est un poisson de jeu populaire, en particulier parmi les pêcheurs qui aiment la pêche à la mouche.

chinesesimp: 美洲鲑(克氏虹鳟)是鲑科的一种鱼类，原产于太平洋、落基山脉和北美大盆地的冷水支流。作为Oncorhynchus属的一员，它是太平洋鳟鱼的一种，包括广泛分布的虹鳟鱼。割喉鳟鱼是受欢迎的游戏鱼，尤其是喜欢飞钓的垂钓者。俗称“割喉”是指下颌下侧与众不同的红色。克拉克ii这个特别的名字是为了纪念探险家威廉·克拉克，他是路易斯和克拉克探险队的队长。

original: The lake trout (Salvelinus namaycush) is a freshwater char living mainly in lakes in northern North America. Other names for it include mackinaw, namaycush, lake char (or charr), touladi, togue, and grey trout. In Lake Superior, it can also be variously known as siscowet, paperbelly and lean. The lake trout is prized both as a game fish and as a food fish. Those caught with dark coloration may be called mud hens.

spanish: La trucha de lago (Salvelinus namaycush) es una especie de char de agua dulce que vive principalmente en lagos del norte de América del Norte. Otros nombres incluyen mackinaw, namaycush, lago char (o charr), touladi, togue y trucha gris. En el Lago Superior, también se le puede conocer como siscowet, paperbelly y lean. La trucha de lago es apreciada como pez de caza y como alimento. Las que se capturan con coloración oscura pueden denominarse gallinas de barro.
french: Le lac Trout (Salvelinus Namaycush) est un charbon douce vivant principalement dans les lacs du nord de l'Amérique du Nord. Les autres noms comprennent Mackinaw, Namaycush, le lac Char (ou Charr), Touladi, Togue et la truite grise. Dans le lac Supérieur, il peut également être connu sous le nom de siscowet, de papier et de maigre. Le truite du lac est prisé à la fois comme un poisson de gibier et comme un poisson alimentaire. Ceux pris avec une coloration foncée peuvent être appelés poules de boue.

chinesesimp: 湖鳟是一种主要生活在北美洲北部湖泊中的淡水鱼。其他名称包括灰鳟。在苏必利尔湖，它也可以被称为剑麻、纸腹和瘦。湖鳟鱼既被视为猎物，也被视为食用鱼。那些颜色较深的可能被称为泥鸡。

portuguese: The sockeye salmon (Oncorhynchus nerka), also called red salmon, kokanee salmon, blueback salmon, or simply sockeye, is an anadromous species of salmon found in the Northern Pacific Ocean and rivers discharging into it. This species is a Pacific salmon that is primarily red in hue during spawning. They can grow up to 84 cm (2 ft 9 in) in length and weigh 2.3 to 7 kg (5–15 lb). Juveniles remain in freshwater until they are ready to migrate to the ocean, over distances of up to 1,600 km (1,000 mi). Their diet consists primarily of zooplankton. Sockeye salmon are semelparous, dying after they spawn. Some populations, referred to as kokanee, do not migrate to the ocean and live their entire lives in fresh water.
chinesesimp: 金鳟也称为红鲑鱼、肯氏红大马哈鱼、蓝背鲑鱼或简称为红鲑，是北太平洋和流入太平洋的河流中发现的溯河产卵的鲑鱼品种。这是一种太平洋鲑鱼，产卵时主要呈红色。它们可以长到84厘米（2英尺9英寸）长，重2.3至7公斤（5-15磅）。幼鱼会一直呆在淡水中，直到它们准备好迁徙到1600公里（1000英里）以外的海洋。它们的食物主要是浮游动物。红鲑是假尾鲑，产卵后死亡。一些被称为kokanee的种群不会迁徙到海洋，它们一生都生活在淡水中。

Juveniles remain in freshwater until they are ready to migrate to the ocean, over distances of up to 1,600 km (1,000 mi). Their diet consists primarily of zooplankton. Sockeye salmon are semelparous, dying after they spawn. Some populations, referred to as kokanee, do not migrate to the ocean and live their entire lives in fresh water.
spanish: El salmón sockeye (Oncorhynchus nerka), también llamado salmón rojo, salmón kokanee, salmón azul o simplemente sockeye, es una especie anádroma de salmón que se encuentra en el océano Pacífico norte y en los ríos que desembocan en él. Esta especie de salmón del Pacífico es principalmente roja durante la desove. Pueden crecer hasta 84 cm (2 pies 9 pulgadas) de largo y pesar entre 2.3 y 7 kg (5-15 lb). Los juveniles permanecen en agua dulce hasta que están listos para migrar al océano, a distancias de hasta 1,600 km (1,000 millas). Su dieta se compone principalmente de zooplancton. El salmón sockeye es semélparo, lo que significa que muere después de desovar. Algunas poblaciones, conocidas como kokanee, no migran al océano y viven toda su vida en agua dulce.
french: Le saumon rouges (Oncorhynchus nerka), également appelé saumon rouge, saumon kokanee, saumon à dos bleu ou simplement saumon, est une espèce anadrome de saumon trouvée dans l'océan Pacifique du Nord et les rivières qui y déchargement. Cette espèce est un saumon du Pacifique qui est principalement rouge dans la teinte pendant le frai. Ils peuvent atteindre 84 cm de long et peser 2,3 à 7 kg. Les juvéniles restent dans l'eau douce jusqu'à ce qu'ils soient prêts à migrer vers l'océan, sur des distances allant jusqu'à 1 600 km. Leur régime se compose principalement de zooplancton. Le saumon rouges est sèche, mourant après avoir frayé. Certaines populations, appelées Kokanee, ne migrent pas vers l'océan et vivent toute leur vie dans l'eau douce.

portuguese: The Chinook salmon Oncorhynchus tshawytscha) is the largest and most valuable species of Pacific salmon in North America, as well as the largest in the genus Oncorhynchus. Its common name is derived from the Chinookan peoples. Other vernacular names for the species include king salmon, Quinnat salmon, Tsumen, spring salmon, chrome hog, Blackmouth, and Tyee salmon. The scientific species name is based on the Russian common name chavycha.

spanish: El salmón chinook (Oncorhynchus tshawytscha), también conocido como salmón rey o salmón gigante, es una especie de salmón del Pacífico. Es el más grande de los salmónidos, pudiendo llegar a medir hasta 1.5 metros de largo y pesar más de 50 kg en casos excepcionales. Esta especie se encuentra en las aguas del océano Pacífico, desde Alaska hasta California, y migra a ríos para desovar, en un proceso conocido como anadromía. Durante el desove, los chinooks cambian de color, pasando de un tono plateado a un color rojizo. Su dieta está compuesta principalmente por peces pequeños, zooplancton y otros invertebrados acuáticos.

original:
Lobsters are malacostracans decapod crustaceans of the family Nephropidae or its synonym Homaridae. They have long bodies with muscular tails and live in crevices or burrows on the sea floor. Three of their five pairs of legs have claws, including the first pair, which are usually much larger than the others. Highly prized as seafood, lobsters are economically important and are often one of the most profitable commodities in the coastal areas they populate.

Commercially important species include two species of Homarus from the northern Atlantic Ocean and scampi (which look more like a shrimp, or a "mini lobster")�the Northern Hemisphere genus Nephrops and the Southern Hemisphere genus Metanephrops.

french: Le bar à petite bouche (Micropterus Dolomieu) est une espèce de poisson d'eau douce dans la famille des poissons-sols (Centrarchidae) de l'Ordre Perciformes. Il s'agit de l'espèce type de son genre Micropterus (basses noires), et est un poisson de jeu populaire recherché par les pêcheurs dans les zones tempérées de l'Amérique du Nord, et s'est propagée par le stockage - ainsi que des introductions illégales - à de nombreux affluents d'eau cool-eau et les lacs au Canada et plus encore introduits aux états-Unis.

original: Centrarchidae, better known as sunfishes, is a family of freshwater ray-finned fish belonging to the order Perciformes (formerly belonging to the deprecated order Centrarchiformes), native only to North America. There are eight universally included genera within the centrarchid family: Lepomis (true sunfishes), Micropterus (black basses), Pomoxis (crappies), Enneacanthus (banded sunfishes), Centrarchus (type genus, consisting solely of the flier C. macropterus), Archoplites (Sacramento perch), Ambloplites (rock basses), and Acantharchus (mud sunfish).

french: La m?le ou poisson-lune (Mola mola) est une espèce de poissons de la famille des Molidae. Sa masse dépasse communément la tonne et peut atteindre 2 744 kilogrammes, ce qui en fait le plus lourd de tous les poissons osseux. On la trouve dans les eaux tropicales et tempérées tout autour du monde. C'est un animal à la tête proéminente, sans queue et latéralement aplati. Nageoires dorsale et anale comprises, une m?le peut être aussi haute que longue.

original: The walleye (Sander vitreus, synonym Stizostedion vitreum), also called the yellow pike or yellow pickerel, is a freshwater perciform fish native to most of Canada and to the Northern United States. It is a North American close relative of the European zander, also known as the pikeperch. The walleye is sometimes called the yellow walleye to distinguish it from the blue walleye, which is a color morph that was once found in the southern Ontario and Quebec regions, but is now presumed extinct.

original: The mahi-mahi  or common dolphinfish (Coryphaena hippurus) is a surface-dwelling ray-finned fish found in off-shore temperate, tropical, and subtropical waters worldwide. It is also widely called dorado (not to be confused with Salminus brasiliensis, a freshwater fish) and dolphin (not to be confused with the aquatic mammal dolphin). It is one of two members of the family Coryphaenidae, the other being the pompano dolphinfish. These fish are most commonly found in the waters around the Gulf of Mexico, Costa Rica, Hawaii, and the Indian Ocean.

original: The sailfish is one or two species of marine fish in the genus Istiophorus, which belong to the family Istiophoridae (marlins). They are predominantly blue to gray in colour and have a characteristically large dorsal fin known as the sail, which often stretches the entire length of the back. Another notable characteristic is the elongated rostrum (bill) consistent with that of other marlins and the swordfish, which together constitute what are known as billfish in sport fishing circles. Sailfish live in colder pelagic waters of all Earth's oceans, and hold the record for the highest speed of any marine animal.
